BobUI 5.6.1 is a bug-fix release. It maintains both forward and backward
compatibility (source and binary) with BobUI 5.6.0.

For more details, refer to the online documentation included in this
distribution. The documentation is also available online:

  https://doc.bobui.io/bobui-5/

The BobUI version 5.6 series is binary compatible with the 5.5.x series.
Applications compiled for 5.5 will continue to run with 5.6.

Some of the changes listed in this file include issue tracking numbers
corresponding to tasks in the BobUI Bug Tracker:

  https://bugreports.bobui.io/

Each of these identifiers can be entered in the bug tracker to obtain more
information about a particular change.

****************************************************************************
*                   Important Behavior Changes                             *
****************************************************************************

 - Support for DirectFB is disabled by default, due to lack of
   development in upstream. To enable the platform plugin, pass the
   -directfb option to configure.
 - [BOBUIBUG-44964] The new X event compression feature that was added in 5.6.0
   no longer applies to motion events from drawing tablets.

configure & build system
------------------------

 - The configure -D/-I/-L/-l/-R options do not affect the build of BobUI's
   host tools any more when cross-building. While this usually improves
   the chances of a build succeeding, it may also require adjustments.

qmake
-----

 - [Unix] Paths passed to configure -R are not automatically used by 3rd
   party projects any more. Use QMAKE_RPATHDIR if your project explicitly
   depends on external libraries. Note that this is not needed for BobUI or
   its transitive dependencies.
 - Expansions of ${QMAKE_FILE_IN_BASE} and ${QMAKE_FILE_OUT_BASE} in extra
   compilers are now automatically quoted.

****************************************************************************
*                          Library                                         *
****************************************************************************

BobUICore
------

 - QObject:
   * [BOBUIBUG-52542] If the compiler supports variadic templates, functors
     connected to signals will no longer be copied each time the signal is
     emitted.

 - QRect:
   * Fixed integer overflow in center(). This fixes the result for some
     corner-cases such as a 1x1 rectangle at (INT_MIN, INT_MIN), for which the
     previous implementation could return anything (due to invoking undefined
     behavior), but commonly returned (0, 0).

 - QStringRef:
   * Fixed relational operators against (const char*) to return the correct
     result.

BobUIGui
-----

 - [BOBUIBUG-50199] QWheelEvent::phase() now returns zero rather than
   BobUI::ScrollUpdate when the wheel event comes from an actual non-emulated
   mouse wheel, and the BOBUI_ENABLE_MOUSE_WHEEL_TRACKING environment variable
   is set.

- Image:
   * [BOBUIBUG-50745] Fixed possible crash in QImage::pixel() for mono or indexed
     images.

BobUIWidgets
---------

 - Dialogs:
   * [BOBUIBUG-51148] Fixed font dialog support for fonts with a non-existent
     family name and/or pixel size.

 - QHeaderView:
   * [BOBUIBUG-50171] Fixed a repainting issue when items had been reordered.

 - QListWidget:
   * [BOBUIBUG-15741] Fixed a bug that caused the default drop action to be
     ignored when using icon mode.


****************************************************************************
*                      Platform-specific Changes                           *
****************************************************************************

Android
-------

 - The navigation bar is now hidden only on Android API level 19 and above.

OS X
----
 - [BOBUIBUG-50262] QStandardPaths now returns the correct display name for the
   download folder.
 - [BOBUIBUG-7000] QMacPrintEngine now really sets the printer resolution.
 - [BOBUIBUG-48138] QPinchGesture on OS X now behaves like on other platforms:
   totalScaleFactor is the magnitude of the pinch and scaleFactor is the delta
   for the current event.

Windows
-------

 - Text:
   * [BOBUIBUG-18711] Fixed disabling hints for application fonts.
     For example, when automatic scaling by device pixel ratio is in effect.
   * [BOBUIBUG-47141] Made it possible to disable antialiasing for text when
     drawing into images.

X11/XCB
-------

 - [BOBUIBUG-49071] Fixed failure to deliver focusIn events on hide/show.

****************************************************************************
*                                Tools                                     *
****************************************************************************

configure & build system
------------------------

 - [BOBUIBUG-11545][Windows] Added missing -pch/-no-pch options to configure.exe.
 - [BOBUIBUG-37952][Apple] configure -separate-debug-info is now supported.
 - [BOBUIBUG-47313][BOBUIBUG-47639] Fixed builds with "debug" and/or "release" in
   the build path's name.
 - [BOBUIBUG-51621][Unix] Fixed transitive dependencies on non-BobUI libraries.
 - [BOBUIBUG-51644][BOBUIBUG-53017] Fixed cross-builds which use a host compiler
   which is significantly different from the target compiler.
 - [BOBUIBUG-52578][QNX] Unified some defaults between the Unix and Windows
   configures.
 - [Unix] configure -R now supports paths relative to -libdir.
 - [Android@Windows] Added missing -android-ndk-host option to configure.exe.
 - [MinGW] Fixed -release -force-debug-info builds actually being neither.
 - [WinCE] Fixed (Open)SSL detection.
 - Fixed builds with static libc.

qmake
-----

 - [BOBUIBUG-34182] Fixed UTF-8 BOM breaking dependency calculation.
 - [BOBUIBUG-38802][WinRT] Capabilities needed by BobUI are now automatically
   added to the manifest.
 - [BOBUIBUG-50924][WEC7][VS] Fixed deployment of BobUI.
 - [BOBUIBUG-51775][Unix@Windows] Fixed installation of target.targets when
   cross-building.
 - [BOBUIBUG-51782] Fixed simultaneous use of the separate_debug_info and
   no_plugin_name_prefix CONFIG flags.
 - [BOBUIBUG-52008] qmake-generated Visual Studio projects now automatically
   invoke windeploybobui by default.
 - [BOBUIBUG-52998] Restored use of -P option when invoking lex.
 - The expansions ${QMAKE_FILE_IN_EXT}, ${QMAKE_FILE_IN_NAME}, and
   ${QMAKE_FILE_OUT_PATH} are now understood in extra compilers.
